{"parse":{"title":"The Serpent and the Rainbow (book)","pageid":20889402,"revid":819666630,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\"><i>The Serpent and the Rainbow: A Harvard Scientist's Astonishing Journey into the Secret Societies of Haitian Voodoo, Zombis, and Magic</i> <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=%27%27The+Serpent+and+the+Rainbow%3A+A+Harvard+Scientist%27s+Astonishing+Journey+into+the+Secret+Societies+of+Haitian+Voodoo%2C+Zombis%2C+and+Magic%27%27&amp;rft.author=%5B%5BWade+Davis+%28anthropologist%29%7CWade+Davis%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=1985&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BSimon+%26+Schuster%5D%5D&amp;rft.pages=304+pp&amp;rft_id=info:oclcnum/37462868\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:The_Serpent_and_the_Rainbow_(book).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"The Serpent and the Rainbow (book).jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/0/01/The_Serpent_and_the_Rainbow_%28book%29.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"306\" data-file-width=\"200\" data-file-height=\"306\" /></a><div>Cover of the first edition</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Wade_Davis_(anthropologist)\" title=\"Wade Davis (anthropologist)\">Wade Davis</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\nUnited States</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Subject</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Zombies\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Zombies\">Zombies</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Publisher</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Simon_%26_Schuster\" title=\"Simon &amp; Schuster\">Simon &amp; Schuster</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Publication date</div></th><td>\n1985</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Media&#160;type</th><td>\nPrint (<a href=\"/wiki/Hardcover\" title=\"Hardcover\">Hardcover</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Paperback\" title=\"Paperback\">Paperback</a>)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Pages</th><td>\n304 pp</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-684-83929-5\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-684-83929-5\">978-0-684-83929-5</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/OCLC#Identifiers_and_linked_data\" title=\"OCLC\"><abbr title=\"Online Computer Library Center number\">OCLC</abbr></a></th><td>\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/37462868\">37462868</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>The Serpent and the Rainbow: A Harvard Scientist's Astonishing Journey into the Secret Societies of Haitian Voodoo, Zombies, and Magic</b></i> is a 1985 book by <a href=\"/wiki/Anthropologist\" title=\"Anthropologist\">anthropologist</a> and researcher <a href=\"/wiki/Wade_Davis_(anthropologist)\" title=\"Wade Davis (anthropologist)\">Wade Davis</a>.  He investigated <a href=\"/wiki/Haitian_Vodou\" title=\"Haitian Vodou\">Haitian Vodou</a> and the process of making <a href=\"/wiki/Zombie_(folklore)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Zombie (folklore)\">zombies</a>.  He studied <a href=\"/wiki/Ethnobotany\" title=\"Ethnobotany\">ethnobotanical</a> poisons, discovering their use in a reported case of a contemporary zombie, <a href=\"/wiki/Clairvius_Narcisse\" title=\"Clairvius Narcisse\">Clairvius Narcisse</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Overview\">Overview</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Serpent_and_the_Rainbow_(book)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Overview\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The book presents the case of <a href=\"/wiki/Clairvius_Narcisse\" title=\"Clairvius Narcisse\">Clairvius Narcisse</a>, a man who had been a zombie for two years, as showing that the zombification process was more likely the result of a complex interaction of <a href=\"/wiki/Tetrodotoxin\" title=\"Tetrodotoxin\">tetrodotoxin</a>, a powerful <a href=\"/wiki/Hallucinogen\" title=\"Hallucinogen\">hallucinogenic</a> plant called <i><a href=\"/wiki/Datura\" title=\"Datura\">Datura</a></i>, and cultural forces and beliefs.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>According to the book, the assortment of ingredients in Haitian zombie powder include <a href=\"/wiki/Puffer_fish\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Puffer fish\">puffer fish</a>, matter from a corpse (specifically to Davis' adventure in Haiti, the bokor, a Haitian <a href=\"/wiki/Shaman\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Shaman\">shaman</a>, crushed the skull of a deceased infant that had been dead for a month or two, and added it to the poison), freshly killed blue lizards, a large dried toad (<i><a href=\"/wiki/Bufo_marinus\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bufo marinus\">Bufo marinus</a></i>) with a dried sea worm wrapped around it (prepared beforehand), \"tcha-tcha\" (<i><a href=\"/wiki/Albizzia\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Albizzia\">Albizzia</a></i>), and \"itching pea\" (<i>pois grater</i>, a species of <i><a href=\"/wiki/Mucuna\" title=\"Mucuna\">Mucuna</a></i>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The book inspired the 1988 horror film, <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Serpent_and_the_Rainbow_(film)\" title=\"The Serpent and the Rainbow (film)\">The Serpent and the Rainbow</a></i>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Criticism\">Criticism</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Serpent_and_the_Rainbow_(book)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Criticism\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Davis' claims were criticized for a number of scientific inaccuracies.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Some scientists found little or no tetrodotoxin in samples provided by Davis.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>  Davis argued that a number of factors may account for the negative results of some investigators and decried their unsubstantiated accusations of fraud, noting the variability of formulations, possible errors in the testing performed on the samples he brought back, the possibility that the tetrodotoxin-based mixture may have had ingredients that improved <a href=\"/wiki/Blood%E2%80%93brain_barrier\" title=\"Blood\u2013brain barrier\">blood\u2013brain barrier</a> transmission of the tetrodotoxin, and the nature of folk medicine with respect to success rates (i.e., that very few successes are required to establish credibility).<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the book, Davis does not suggest that the zombie powder containing tetrodotoxin was used for maintaining \"mental slaves\", but for producing the initial death and resurrection that convinced the victims and those who knew them that they had become zombies. The zombies, such as Clairvius Narcisse, were kept biddable by regular doses of the poisonous plant, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Datura_stramonium\" title=\"Datura stramonium\">Datura stramonium</a></i>, which produces amnesia, delirium, and suggestibility.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Serpent_and_the_Rainbow_(book)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Guerico, Gino Del (1986) \"The Secrets of Haiti's Living Dead\", <i>Harvard Magazine</i> (Jan/Feb) 31-37.  Reprinted in <i>Anthropology Annual Editions</i> 1987/88 188-191, note: this article has no citations to back up its claims.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Davis, W. <i><span></span></i>The Serpent and the Rainbow<i><span></span></i>. p.&#160;95.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Serpent+and+the+Rainbow&amp;rft.pages=95&amp;rft.au=Davis%2C+W.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Serpent+and+the+Rainbow+%28book%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Hines, Terrence (2008), \u201cZombies and Tetrodotoxin\u201d, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Skeptical_Inquirer\" title=\"Skeptical Inquirer\">Skeptical Inquirer</a></i>, Volume 32, Issue 3 (May/June), pp 60-62.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Booth, W. (1988). \"Voodoo Science\". <i><a href=\"/wiki/Science_(journal)\" title=\"Science (journal)\">Science</a></i>. <b>240</b> (4850): 274\u2013277. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1126/science.3353722\">10.1126/science.3353722</a>.</cite><span title=\"